From: Erik Hugne <erik.hugne@ericsson.com>
Subject: [PATCH 17/17] tipc: bump tipc_ports kconfig limit/default
Patch-mainline: never
References: bsc#907063
Acked-by: Jiri Bohac <jbohac@suse.cz>

Dynamic reconfiguration of the amount of TIPC ports is not
possible to backport to the 3.0.* kernel due to a chain
of dependencies, which leads to kernel API functions missing in
the older kernels.
This workaround changes the max/default to 128k in the Kconfig.

Signed-off-by: Erik Hugne <erik.hugne@ericsson.com>
---
 net/tipc/Kconfig |    6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/tipc/Kconfig b/net/tipc/Kconfig
index c890848..4469832 100644
--- a/net/tipc/Kconfig
+++ b/net/tipc/Kconfig
@@ -23,11 +23,11 @@ menuconfig TIPC
 config TIPC_PORTS
 	int "Maximum number of ports in a node"
 	depends on TIPC
-	range 127 65535
-	default "8191"
+	range 127 131071
+	default "131071"
 	help
 	  Specifies how many ports can be supported by a node.
-	  Can range from 127 to 65535 ports; default is 8191.
+	  Can range from 127 to 131071 ports; default is 131071.
 
 	  Setting this to a smaller value saves some memory,
 	  setting it to higher allows for more ports.
